    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_404359">Does 3.5 really have enough flaws for it to need a revision? It's not like the 2nd to 3rd edition leap where they made massive improvements. I realized this when I decided to replay the Baldur's Gate games and found myself trying to remember the difference between dual and multi classing, the counterintuitive stat system, and thac0s. The difference between 18 strength and 19 strength is apparently a much larger value of 1 than the difference between 17 and 18. And instead of just doing the obvious method of getting a per level bonus to your attack rolls and having to roll higher than the armor class to hit, they somehow decided on something that is mathematically the exact same thing only in a much more convoluted backwards manner.</div>
