My friends and I are doing a palladium campaign now, both evil and good, same world, same story line, though we are doing the evil side more..<br />
<br />
<br />
I'm a Raksasha, a heavily nerfed one at that.. oh well, as i level i'll get to the power of a true raksasha. <br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
oh man... i have a great story.. we were clearing out a mine of goblins for some money(i wanted to burn the town.. but the rest of my party opted to clear the mine for money.) We killed 5 goblins in a passage, there was a ramp going up leading to a tunnel where we entered, and a tunnel going down the passage, we set up 3 of the corpses on the ramp. Long story short, almost every goblin coming to hit us from the ramp tripped over the corpses and were on the floor for half the melee, it was quite funny. We have a soldier who, if you put Fighter from 8-bit theater into this game, you'd wouldn't be able to tell them apart, even though this soldier has an iq of 15(now -2 to it due to various funny reasons.)<br />
<br />
<br />
this entire campaign is turning into a comedy... unintentionally of course.<br />
<br />
<br />
Oh yea, on the good campaign, we have an assassin who the gm allowed to roll on spitting at this imp... he rolled a 20.. it was after this &quot;epic&quot; battle in a watch tower at a keep... he had 1 hp left. Our good campaign characters are in a dungeon in said keep right now... being watched over by a beholder. A very powerful beholder.</div>
