    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_404484">Well if you think about it, new editions really just give people more options.  You can still use your old edition if you like (though I guess eventually they'll become  hard to come by since publishing will likely cease).<br />
<br />
For some people, new books are like getting new gear in an MMO, a reward or upgrade that drives the experience.  Others just like the new fluff, pictures, ideas, etc...<br />
<br />
I also don't really blame WOTC.  It's so easy to download / fileshare their products.  Technology, in a way, cheated them out of a lot of the money they'd have gotten for 3.5, and really pushes along the need for more updates to the core stuff so that people feel compelled to buy it.<br />
<br />
They are a business after all<br />
<br />
-Slathe</div>
